# Hook File Conventions

All custom hooks must follow this structure:

- Root folder: `hooks/` (never `hook/`)
- Group related hooks in a themed subfolder: `hooks/<theme>/`
- Each file is named `use-<name>.hook.ts`

## Examples

```
hooks/device-motion/use-device-motion.hook.ts
hooks/auth/use-auth.hook.ts
hooks/zones/use-zones.hook.ts
```

## Rules

- Never place hook files directly in `hooks/` — always use a subfolder
- The subfolder name and file name should share the same theme/name
- File name must start with `use-`
- Import using the full path: `import { useDeviceMotion } from '@/hooks/device-motion/use-device-motion.hook'`
